This is a simplified version of Conway's slide puzzle.

Ths puzzle is introducedby John H. Conway [1], who is a British mathematician, professor in Princeton Univeristy[2]. Consider the below settings:


1 ---- [ ] -----7
|       |       |
2       |       6
|       |       |
3 ----- 4 ------5

Using the empty cell to slide the numbers. The target is to reverse the order of these numbers.

7 ---- [ ] -----1
|       |       |
6       |       1
|       |       |
5 ----- 4 ------3

[1]. http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Horton_Conway
[2]. Tan Xiangbai, ``Interesting math''. ISBN: 9787514804317, 7514804315